This document describes how the application is deployed using Kubernetes and ArgoCD following GitOps principles.

The system is designed so that:

All infrastructure and application configuration live in Git
ArgoCD continuously reconciles the cluster state with Git
Deployments are automated, repeatable, and auditable
🏗️ Deployment Architecture
GitHub (source of truth)
        ↓
ArgoCD (GitOps controller)
        ↓
Kubernetes (k3s cluster)
        ↓
Application Pods (React app)
⚙️ Kubernetes Setup

The application is deployed into a dedicated namespace to ensure isolation and manageability.

Core components deployed:

Deployment → manages application pods and scaling
Service → exposes the application internally
Ingress (Traefik) → handles external routing and HTTPS
TLS configuration → enables secure access
🔐 Private Container Registry Integration

The application image is stored in a private container registry (GHCR).

Key requirement:

Kubernetes must authenticate before pulling the image.

Solution:
A Kubernetes imagePullSecret is created using a GitHub token
The deployment references this secret to securely pull images
🚀 ArgoCD (GitOps Workflow)

ArgoCD is responsible for:

Monitoring the Git repository
Detecting changes in Kubernetes manifests
Applying those changes automatically to the cluster
🔁 Deployment Flow
Developer pushes code to GitHub
CI pipeline builds and pushes a Docker image to GHCR
Kubernetes manifests in the repo reference the new image
ArgoCD detects the change
ArgoCD syncs the cluster to match Git
Kubernetes pulls the image and updates the running application
🔄 Sync Strategy

The application uses automated sync with:

Auto Sync → deploy changes automatically
Prune → remove resources deleted from Git
Self-Heal → correct drift between cluster and desired state

This ensures the cluster always reflects the Git repository.

⚠️ Issues Encountered & Resolutions
1. ImagePullBackOff (401 Unauthorized)

Cause:

Image stored in private registry
Kubernetes lacked authentication

Resolution:

Created imagePullSecret
Linked it to the deployment
Restarted pods to re-trigger image pull
2. ArgoCD OutOfSync

Cause:

Resources existed in cluster but were removed from Git

Resolution:

Enabled pruning during sync
Ensured Git is the single source of truth
3. Incorrect Repository Path

Cause:

ArgoCD scanning entire repo including non-Kubernetes files

Resolution:

Scoped ArgoCD to the k8s/ directory only
4. Duplicate Application Creation

Cause:

Application defined both in UI and Git

Resolution:

Switched fully to Git-managed ArgoCD configuration
📂 Repository Structure (Relevant to Deployment)
k8s/        → Kubernetes manifests
docs/       → Documentation

ArgoCD is configured to track only the k8s/ directory.

